cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the concept of network slicing in the context of 5G networks, which is primarily related to networking and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of SDN and NFV technologies, which are related to information technology (cs.IT) and architecture (cs.AR). The paper also addresses the challenges associated with network slicing, which can be considered as a system-level issue (cs.SY) and may involve data center technologies (cs.DC).
